 Recently there have been several      
 changes in the shops in Thornbury. A  
 new supermarket, Safeways opened in   
 1983 causing some of the smaller shops
 to close down. On-site bakeries are a 
 current trend.                        
{A SUMMARY OF THORNBURY'S SHOPS}       
 Antique 2;Art and Craft 1;Auto part 3;
 Bakers 4;Butchers 3; Carpets 1;       
 Chemists 4; Clothes 6; Cycle 1;       
 Electrical 5; Food shops 3; Garage 1  
 Garden 1; Gift Shops 4; Greengrocers 3
 Hardware 5; Healthfoods 1;Jeweller 2; 
 Kitchen 1;Newsagents 3;Off-licence 2; 
 Oxfam 1;Pet 1;Post Office 1; Sewing & 
 Wool 2;Shoe 3; Sports 2; Stationery 1;
 Sweet shop 1.                         
{From a survey}we found that most      
 people shop by car. Shoppers consider 
 convenience and economy important.    
{Safeways}seems to be the shop with the
 most trade.
